commit.message: Update version number and copyright year.

Add several pdf engines.

Tectonic, latexmk and pagedjs-cli have been added as options for pdf generation in Pandoc.
Add a `declare-function` for `ebib`.

Remove call to `easy-menu-add`.

The function is deprecated and has been a no-op for a long time.
Move *all* deprecated options to the bottom of their submenus.

Fix doc string of `pandoc--latest-run`.

Doc strings should not be wider than 80 characters.
Move obsolete options to the bottom of their submenus.
Always create an output file for pptx output.

Fix `pandoc-jump-to-reference`.

Add an extra grouping to `pandoc-regex-citation-key` and update
`pandoc-jump-to-reference` accordingly.

This should fix Github issue #107.

Add `defaults` to `pandoc--cli-options`.

Without this, `defaults` is ignored in the call to pandoc. This should fix
Github issue #106.
Make sure fontification of citation keys does not override other fontification.

Fix pandoc-regex-citation-key.

In a character alternative, the hyphen should appear last.

Remove font-lock faces for citations save for the key.

The existing regexps are too greedy, see Github issue #105. A closer look
revealed that in citations with multiple keys, they actually match the wrong
thing: only one key is really matched as a key, the others are matched as extra
material (prefix, locator or suffix in CSL parlance).

Fixing this is difficult,[1] so it seems best to just font-lock the key itself
for now so that at least issue #105 is fixed. We can always revisit the problem
later.

[1] <https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/help-gnu-emacs/2021-03/msg00104.html>

Update for Pandoc version 2.12

- Add `org` as a possible format for the extension `task_list`.
- Change `resource-path` from a string option to a list option.

The latter change will cause an error for users that use this option, but the
code isn't very amenable to adding a check for the type of the `resource-path`
option's value. There is no clear place in the code where it could be added. The
logical place would be `pandoc--read-settings-from-file`, but it reads the
settings with `read` in one go.
Add code comment explaining the previous commit.

Add filters to the command line before other options.

Apparently, the order of filters w.r.t. other options may be relevant, see
Github issue #104. This commit should fix the problem in that particular issue.
If more fine-grained control turns out to be necessary in the future, we'll need
to think about how to do this.

Store list and alist options in the order given.

This ensures that they are passed to `pandoc` in the order that the user enters
them.
Manual: add note about defaults files and YAML metadata.
Bug fix: fix doc string of `pandoc-file-hydra`.
Add option `markdown-headings`.
Add option --citeproc
